<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1071] Set index interval at flush time based off count of keys and key attributes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1071</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From Andrew Purtell note up on list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Later, maybe it would make sense to dynamically set the index&lt;br/&gt;
interval based on the distribution of cell sizes in the &lt;br/&gt;
mapfile at some future time, according to some parameterized&lt;br/&gt;
formula that could be adjusted with config variable(s). This&lt;br/&gt;
could be done during compaction. Would make sense to also&lt;br/&gt;
consider the distribution of key lengths. Or there could be&lt;br/&gt;
other similar tricks implemented to keep index sizes down. &quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12411090">HBASE-1071</key>
            <summary>Set index interval at flush time based off count of keys and key attributes</summary>
