                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12658282" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 20 Dec 2008 12:54:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One way to approach this is to estimate the size of the index on the heap by key count and lengths. Then consider a certain limit, and increase the index interval as necessary until the estimated index size is below threshold. This is simple and gives only one knob &amp;#8211; easy enough to tweak &amp;#8211; that gets directly to the effect wanted.  Then a suitable default can be found through testing of some educated guesses with PE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711276" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 May 2009 18:25:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving invalid.  We no longer have intervals in our size-based index.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
